WETH is the ERC-20 compatible version of ether.

1 #ETH = 1WETH and vice versa. 
1 #BTC = 1WBTC and vice versa.

What is #WETH? 

Ethere, Ethereum's native currency was created before the ERC-20 standard was implemented. (ERC20 is a standard for issuing smart contracts on #ETH.) 

So, there isn't ERC-20 compatible and can't be directly exchanged for ERC-20 tokens.

What is #WBTC?

As the #Bitcoin & #Ethereum blockchains were created at different times, they can't easily communicate. WBTC is an #Ethereum token that represents #BTC. It enables the use of BTC on the #ETH network. 

Its main benefit is its compatibility with the DeFi space.

What is their purpose? 

Different blockchains offer different functionality & aren't always compatible. For example, you can't use #BTC or #Eth. Wrapped tokens allow non-native tokens to be used on different blockchains. 

They can act as bridges between different blockchains.
